{"id":"furrow","term":"Furrow","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>An opening in the ground made by the plough (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 65:10\">Ps. 65:10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hosea 10:4\">Hos. 10:4</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hosea 10:10\">10</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Psalms 65:10","Hosea 10:4","Hosea 10:10"]}